      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-27 21:39:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(5 inline comments)\n\nCould you imagine a reproducer for the bug we can add to sanity or racer ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "91081103494a01f0fedfb9e8b00637bb2a95b648",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-28 18:05:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (3 inline comments)\n\nThe root cause of the problem is that the layout changed from an empty layout to raid1 in the middle of an active IO. We used to use refcount of lsm to account for active IO and this turns out bloody wrong because empty layout files don't have a lsm.\n\nIt's possible to work out a test case, but it will need a couple of delay to make it happen at right time. I'm okay to live without it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
